Elixir/Phoenix:
- [ ] No `Code.eval_string()` or `:erlang.binary_to_term()` with untrusted input
- [ ] Ecto queries use parameterized fragments — no string interpolation in SQL
- [ ] Phoenix controllers validate and sanitize all user input via changesets
- [ ] GenServer `handle_call`/`handle_cast` includes timeout or handles unexpected messages
- [ ] No sensitive data in Logger output (tokens, passwords, PII)
- [ ] LiveView assigns are minimized — no large data structures pushed to the socket
- [ ] HEEx templates (Phoenix 1.7+ / LiveView 0.18+): `{expression}` is valid for BOTH attribute values AND text content — do NOT flag this as an error. The legacy `<%= expression %>` form also works but `{expression}` is the modern syntax
